&lt;h1 id="we-cant-prove-most-theorems-with-known-physics"&gt;We Can’t Prove Most Theorems with Known Physics&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Apr 14 2021&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Unprovable theorems vastly outnumber the provable ones&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Brett:&lt;/strong&gt;
The overwhelming majority of theorems in mathematics are theorems that we cannot possibly prove. This is &lt;a href=""&gt;Gödel’s theorem&lt;/a&gt;, and it also comes out of &lt;a href=""&gt;Turing’s proof&lt;/a&gt; of what is and is not computable.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>